# 🐞 bug report

### Affected Package

"@angular/http": "^7.2.15"

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

Using angular/http, Typescript truncates the last digits of a int64 type retrieved via HTTP, due to number being a floating point number type. Using the new `bigint` data type https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/release-notes/typescript-3-2.html#bigint yields the same result in my testings. Is there a possibility to handle int64 without truncation by the `number` type through angular http?

