# 🐞 Bug report

### Command (mark with an `x`)
<!-- Can you pin-point the command or commands that are effected by this bug? -->
<!-- ✍️edit: -->
```
- [x] build
```

### Description
When both Ivy and the `vendorChunk` options are turned on, some JIT code isn't being tree shaken from production bundles. The code gets removed correctly if the `vendorChunk` option is turned off.


## 🔬 Minimal Reproduction
To reproduce the issue  and run `ng build --prod`. Once the build is finished, go to the `dist` directory and open the `vendor` bundle.

1. [Clone this repo](https://github.com/crisbeto/ivy-tree-shaking-bug).
2. Run `npm install`.
3. Run `ng build --prod`.
4. Go into the `dist` directory and open the `vendor` bundle file. It should be called something like `vendor-es5.e7633243d6659fd2e6e7.js`.
5. Prettify the file so it's more readable.

At this point try doing a code search for `ng:///`. You should get some code that looks like this:

```js
Object.defineProperty(t, ie, {
configurable: !0,
get: function () {
    return null === i && (i = It().compileNgModule(_p, "ng:///" + t.name + "/ngModuleDef.js", {
    type: t,
    bootstrap: qt(e.bootstrap || bp).map(gt),
    declarations: r.map(gt),
    imports: qt(e.imports || bp).map(gt).map(Sp),
    exports: qt(e.exports || bp).map(gt).map(Sp),
    emitInline: !0,
    schemas: e.schemas ? qt(e.schemas) : null,
    id: e.id || null
    })), i
}
});
```

Since the code is mangled it's a little hard to tell, but these `ng:///` strings come from some JIT-specific code in `@angular/core` that is originally here: https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/master/packages/core/src/render3/jit/directive.ts#L108. This code is only relevant in JIT mode and it shouldn't be in the AOT-compiled production bundle. 

To illustrate the point that the `vendorChunk` option is causing the code to be retained, you can turn off the `vendorChunk` flag in the `angular.json`, run the build again and observe that the code isn't there anymore.

Also this project was created by running `ng new` and then changing the `vendorChunk` option in the `angular.json`.

